## Code Style & Standards

### Coding Standard
- **Style guide**: {{STYLE_GUIDE}} (e.g., Google C++, LLVM, Mozilla)
- **Naming**: {{NAMING_CONVENTION}}
  - Classes: PascalCase or UpperCamelCase
  - Functions: camelCase or snake_case
  - Variables: camelCase or snake_case
  - Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE or kConstantName
  - Namespaces: lowercase

### Header Organization
{{HEADER_ORGANIZATION}}
<!--
Example:
- Header guards: `#pragma once` or `#ifndef HEADER_H`
- Include order: System headers → Third-party → Project headers
- Forward declarations: Use to reduce compile time
- Inline functions: In headers when small
-->

### Code Quality
- **Linter**: {{LINTER}} (clang-tidy, cppcheck, cpplint)
- **Formatter**: {{FORMATTER}} (clang-format)
